io.deepstream

Class AnonymousRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.deepstream.AnonymousRecord

  • public class AnonymousRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    An AnonymousRecord is a record without a predefined name. It acts like a wrapper around an actual record that can be swapped out for another one whilst keeping all bindings intact. Imagine a customer relationship management system with a list of users on the left and a user detail panel on the right. The user detail panel could use the anonymous record to set up its bindings, yet whenever a user is chosen from the list of existing users the anonymous record's setName method is called and the detail panel will update to show the selected user's details
